## Non-Negotiable Contract Rules

- Use one adaptive Layout section with scaling rules (no
  multiple named layout variants).
- Merge recipe guidance into Layout and/or Block slot map (no
  separate layout-recipe section).
- Keep canonical heading order:
  1. Table of contents
  2. Core rule
  3. Writing guidance
  4. Layout
  5. Available slot shapes
  6. Render skeleton
  7. Common mistakes (and fixes)
  8. Structural preflight rules (must pass)
  9. Split policy rules
  10. Full example
- Render skeleton must be fully copy-ready with complete
  placeholder sentences.
- Full example must be fully worked (filled values), not a
  lightly edited skeleton.
- Active voice, complete sentences, client-ready tone; no
  fragmented bullets.
- Do not use process/meta phrasing (e.g., extraction/process
  notes).
- If a schedule/table exists, do not add a “comments” column;
  explanations belong in rationale text.
- Keep final references self-contained to skill/kpmg-fdd; do
  not add links to external folders in contract text.

## Section-Specific Fidelity

- Follow GUIDANCE_FILE first, then corpus style patterns.
- Use corpus as wording/structure evidence only; do not copy
